«IN MEMORY OF
BERT SMITH
WHO SERVED THE VILLAGE IN
SO MANY VARIED WAYS
36 YEARS AS A COUNCILLOR
CHAIRMAN FROM 1983 - 1987
18 YEARS AS CHAIRMAN OF THE FORESHORE COMMITTEE
CHURCH WARDEN EMERITUS
THIS SEAT WAS DONATED BY THE FAMILY

KEN AND WIN STANBURY
WHO LOVED CHARMOUTH
27-02-1920 - 18-02-2002
27-05-1918 - 18-06-2013

In memory of Mike Burrows
who liked to sit here and eat ice cream
while watching the sea

In memory of Jackson Falla
2010 - 2020
Forever in our hearts

In loving memory of Frank and Ruth Burborough,
who shared lots of happy
times in Charmouth and Dorset.
Always missed
XXX

MILLSTONES
THE TWO MILLSTONES WEIGHING
APPROXIMATELY 1 1/4 TONS EACH WERE 
USED IN THE FACTORY ON THE
FORESHORE IN THE PRODUCTION OF CEMENT
FROM 1850-1867. LIMESTONE COLLECTED
FROM THE BEACH THEN CRUSHED BY
THE MILLSTONES WHICH WERE POWERED
BY A STEAM ENGINE, THE CRUSHED LIMESTONE
THEN BEING CALCINED IN KILNS."┐
